{
  "bookId": "laozi-wangbi-wiki",
  "num": 13,
  "title": "第十三章",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "寵辱若驚，貴大患若身。何謂寵辱若驚？寵為下，得之若驚，失之若驚，是謂寵辱若驚。"
    },
    {
      "text": "何謂貴大患若身？"
    },
    {
      "text": "吾所以有大患者，為吾有身，"
    },
    {
      "text": "及吾無身，"
    },
    {
      "text": "吾有何患？故貴以身為天下，若可寄天下；"
    },
    {
      "text": "愛以身為天下，若可託天下。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 39
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "寵必有辱，榮必有患，驚辱等、榮患同也。為下得寵辱榮患若驚，則不足以亂天下也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 8
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "大患，榮寵之屬也。生之厚，必入死之地，故謂之大患也。人迷之於榮寵，返之於身，故曰大患若身也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "由有其身也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "歸之自然也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 19
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無以易其身，故曰貴也。如此乃可以託天下也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無物可以損其身，故曰愛也。如此乃可以寄天下也。不以寵辱榮患損易其身，然後乃可以天下付之也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
